cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.CC, cs.CR, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses QoE in the context of online video delivery and resource sharing in multi-tenant operations. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category as the paper discusses QoE in relation to content. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of QoE modeling and assessment. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper briefly mentions SLAs (Service Level Agreements) which can have security implications. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the relationship between QoS and QoE and how to approach the rest of the QoE beyond what can be inferred from QoS.
